ce:section.ce:para:
Under optimal conditions, the sensitivity of the aptamer sensor was assessed. Fig. 3
                         illustrates the fluorescence intensity in 1 × PBS and saliva as a function of fentanyl concentration, revealing that increased fentanyl levels corresponded with heightened fluorescence intensity, demonstrating a strong linear relationship within the concentration range of 5–1000 nM (in PBS solution) and 10–200 nM (in saliva medium), respectively. In the PBS solution, the linear regression equations were Y = 5.51c + 1917.07 (r = 0.9868) with fentanyl in the concentration range 5–200 nM and Y = 1.14c + 2751.37 (r = 0.9988) with fentanyl in the concentration range 200–1000 nM, with a detection limit of 1.90 nM. In the saliva medium, the linear regression equation was Y = 6.20c + 1266.29 (r = 0.9955) with the LOD of 5.02 nM. Compared to other studies (Table 1
                        ), our fluorescence aptamer sensor distinguished itself through its broad detection range and low detection limit.
